The federal government has given conditions for which the restriction order will be lifted, even as it urged Nigerians to exercise restraint in the face of the lockdown. Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF), Boss Mustapha, stated this yesterday during the daily briefing of the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 in Abuja. He said, “This is a long-term effort and we should exercise patience as we gradually walk out of danger, reopen our society and her economic life. This virus has no vaccine. “Success will mean a return to normalcy and we can only claim victory when cases are no longer increasing, we have no unknown sources for cases, deaths are no longer increasing, and more admissions are discharged. The only path to these is your full collaboration and compliance”. He also disclosed that recent data released by the NCDC has shown a rise in the number of cases in Kano. “The state government has in response to the development imposed a lockdown and curfew in the state. The PTF will visit the state to evaluate the state of readiness and to guide the authorities in the management of the situation,” he added. The SGF also disclosed that the police and other services have launched investigations into the various reports of fake news. He warned all purveyors of fake news to desist as it is capable of misleading the public and causing distraction in government’s collective effort to fight this war.